info.headline: Flood Warning issued June 10 at 10:48PM EDT until June 11 at 11:36PM EDT by NWS Indianapolis IN
info.description:
...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers and locations in Indiana...
East Fork White River at Seymour.
White River at Newberry, Petersburg, Hazleton, Edwardsport, and Elliston.
...The Flood Warning is extended for the following river and location in Indiana...Illinois...
Wabash River at Riverton.
.Recent rainfall amounts of two to four inches across central Indiana continues to produce minor flooding along portions of the East Fork White, White, and Wabash rivers in western Indiana. Flooding will end as late as this coming Saturday in the most southern reaches of the river(s), but as early as tonight on the Wabash at Riverton.
* WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast.
* WHERE...East Fork White River at Seymour.
* WHEN...Until late tomorrow evening.
* IMPACTS...At 12.0 feet, Significant agricultural lands begins to flood. High water affects some local roads.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 9:45 PM EDT Tuesday the stage was 12.7 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 9:45 PM EDT Tuesday was 12.7 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise to a crest of 12.7 feet just after midnight tonight. It will then fall below flood stage late tomorrow morning. - Flood stage is 12.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction:
Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks.
Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the dangers of flooding.
Additional information is available at www.weather.gov/ind.
The next statement should be issued Wednesday afternoon by around 200 PM EDT /100 PM CDT/.
